    "They sped up the training process by integrating batch normalization.",
    "They also optimized the hyper-parameters through an automatic hyper-parameter tuning method in order to improve accuracy.",
    "Pudlitz et al. [29] presented an automated approach for extracting system states from natural language requirements using a self-trained named-entity recognition model with bidirectional LSTMs and CNNs.",
    "They presented a semi-automated technique to extract system state candidates from natural language requirements for the automotive domain.",
    "The results show that their automated approach achieves an F1-score of 0.51, with only 15 min of manual work, while the iterative approach achieves an F1-score of 0.62 with 100 min."
